sub_title: Lecturer Healthcare&Nursing at Rijn IJssel _ Mentor/assessor at HAN Master Physician Assistant _ Molecular Scientist at Radboudumc
summary:
About me: 
I am a passionate Life Science researcher and teacher in Health Care and Nursing Sciences and an inquisitive scientist with a “can-do” mentality. I have an accurate, disciplined, loyal and reliable personality.
Competences:
Education of students in Nursing and Health Sciences
Coaching, co-operating and making new commitments. Exploring new opportunities. 
What motivates me:
Sharing knowledge and learning from students and colleagues. I am a lifelong learner.

After over 20 years of medical and biological research, I now work as a teacher at Rijn IJssel and as coach at the Master HAN (Hogeschool Arnhem Nijmegen). My focus is on teaching laboratory-, writing- and presentation- skills and coaching students on their way to a career in the life sciences, medicine, care and nursing.
I have a heart for medicine, biology, biotechnology and can speak the language of the medical staff, technicians, students, teachers and scientists alike. 
I get energy from Bioscience and Health Care, learning new "stuff and transferring my knowledge to the next generation of professionals and I am a life time learner myself.
